This paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for graphs, which are typically categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the study of graph connectivity, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of pathwidth in the paper suggests a possible categorization under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for a specific problem, which could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
